# list current aliases
alias


# enable alias

## for current terminal session

alias a_name=value
alias a_name='command'
alias a_name='command arg1 arg2'
alias a_name='/path/to/script'
alias a_name='/path/to/script.pl arg1'

## over next terminal sessions
source the alias file in shell init (rc)


# disable alias

## temporarily
\a_name

## permanent
### in session
unalias a_name
### over next terminal sessions
remove source from shell init



sources:
https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/bash-shell-temporarily-disable-an-alias/
https://www.tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/aliases.html
https://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/bash-aliases-mac-centos-linux-unix.html
